# Uint1 overflow tests

(tx 'create schema test')
(tx 'create table test.item(field: uint1)')
!tx 'insert (256) into test.item (field)'
---
> error[PO0001]: value overflows column `field` type `UINT1`
>   1 │ insert (256) into test.item (field)
>     │         ^
>     = value `256` does not fit into `UINT1` (range: 0 to 255)
> 
> note: column `field` is of type `UINT1`
> 
> help: reduce the value, change the column type to a wider type or change the overflow policy
